name: ESG Scores Data
description:
This dataset has ESG scores for different ESG factors for companies. There are 5 kind of files for each factor for each stock:

Ã¢â‚¬Â¢ Pulse files: The files provide scores that measures short-term, real-time performance and focus on events of the day
Ã¢â‚¬Â¢ Insight files:  The files provide scores that are derived from pulse score using an exponentially weighted moving average (WMA) and focuses on measuring long-term performance
Ã¢â‚¬Â¢ Momentum files: Focus on measuring the trend of a company. These scores are derived from Insight Scores by measuring the slope of insight scores.
Ã¢â‚¬Â¢ Volume files: Measures by company the number of unique articles, as well as the number of categories scored daily
Ã¢â‚¬Â¢ Volume ttm  files: Measures by company the number of unique articles, as well as the number of categories scored over last 12 months

name: Growth Valuation Model
description: This dataset is a stock ranking model that sort companies based on valuation ratios. It looks at different valuation ratios & intelligently combines them into a single comprehensive measure of relative valuation. Each ratio is weighed to ensure most important ratio for a stock has greatest influence in final score. It blends information from both reported actuals & analyst estimates over quarterly, semi-annual or annual horizons.

It provides a full term structure of risk for both corporate and sovereign credit names based upon a multiple models approach.

name: Relationship Data for Equity
description: The dataset outputs various classifications and grouping of instruments based on such company connections. Most of grouping fields  are sparse, you may always use densify function such as group_neutralize(alpha, densify(group)) to avoid error while using group operators.

name: Equity Warrants Data
description: The dataset includes globally Equity Warrants  data

name: Intermediate Cluster Groups
description: This is statistical grouping data.

name: Derived Industry Classification
description: This is a statistical grouping data. The prefix "cx" in the field name defines group count such as 2,5,10,20,50. The coverage of fields is also put in their names like sta1_top500c10 has coverage only in TOP500.

name: Alternate Industry Classification
description: This is a statistical grouping data. The prefix "cx" in the field name defines the group count such as 2,5,10,20,50. The coverage of fields is also put in their names like sta2_top500_fact1_c10 has coverage only in TOP500.

name: Equity Interval Data
description: Price Volume related dataset based on assessment dates and values for various financial, operational, and transactional metrics across different sectors and activities.

name: Index Market Data
description: The dataset includes global Index market data

name: Corporate Action Dataset
description: This dataset looks at corporate events that can affect stock prices, such as delisting, merger, stock splits, etc. One can analyze the effect of corporate actions on stock prices and develop alphas based on event-driven opportunities.

name: Securities Lending Insight Data
description: The dataset provides list of metrics, covering lending fee, short interest, it also supplies two unique factors, measuring crowding and short squeeze risks.

name: Short Interest Model
description: This is a model dataset that gives short interest data of stocks. It mainly covers USA stocks but also has some limited coverage in other regions. Investment hypothesis states that stocks with higher/lower number of shares shorted will underperform/outperform their peers. This data normalizes short interest levels across country, market cap, and sector categories and also provides institutional ownership percentage, volatility levels and short squeeze level for stocks.

name: SmartHoldings Model
description: This dataset is a global stock selection model that ranks stocks based on the predicted future change in institutional ownership. It looks into various funds and creates their purchasing profile based on the underlying fundamental or technical factors of the companies it buys. Aggregation over different funds help predict future probable changes in institutional ownership of the stocks.

name: Short Selling Model
description: The dataset combines features obtained from short contracts to estimate risk-neutral returns. The factors include loan rates, volume of loans, age of loans, their differences over time, and so on, and derived factors. The method of combination differs among different type of contracts and regions, and all factors are standardized to percentile. The combined score is a strong alpha mode.

name: Lexical Breakdown Data
description: Sentiment scores derived from social media. Some words or phrases have a sentiment score associated with them, on the basis of these scores the sentiment score of the text is calculated.
